24/08/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski emerged from a meeting with the National Security Council on Thursday (August 23rd) and said there is no information to suggest there are any serious threats to Macedonia's security.
He called on the relevant ministries to watch the situation in the region closely, and to react if necessary.
Much of the session focused on efforts to resolve the final status of neighbouring Kosovo.Crvenkovski warned the international community against allowing the partitioning of Kosovo, saying it would encourage other separatists in the Balkans.
(MIA, A1, AFP, Makfax, Reuters, Xinhua - 23/08/07)
